column14: Measurement likely plots off due to VERY strong wind.  For MGH, it will likely be best to average logger readings because WL did get as high as ~ 0.730m (while observing, not recording WL). @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ On the last visit, I accidentally plugged the sensor tip of the Ott sensor.  As a result, the sensor very slowly adjusted, and we left the station before it did adjust.  Today, the sensor was measured to be about 0.600m below the water and the HG RAW was 0.597m, so the sensor is reading accurately. Large Reset was expected. I took the anchor/sensor up and uncovered the Ott,so the sensor should read accurately and quickly. I put sensor back in the water at 10:53 PST.  Sensor is in water of about 0.52m deep. No second reset due to VERY stron wind conditons Mid-section

column14: @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ After first cut, I pulled up the anchor and ott sensor. The Ott was inside the liquid tite armour. I cut the armout back a little, and took off the cap on the sensor.  There was a little sedment inside the cap. Cleaned it out, and put anchor back in. Ott off set is really low (0.038m), but should be much higher (~0.5m: depth of water at anchor). Some thing odd is happening.  It looks like the offset is taking a long time to adjust.  It seems to go up about 0-.005m every 5 minutes. It'll take hours to adjust.  I'll have to adjust it in Aquarius later. Mid-section
